# ── AI-assisted review hooks — derived skill directories ───────────────────
# .skills/ is the canonical, tool-neutral source of truth and IS committed.
# The directories below are per-developer derived copies produced by
# scripts/sync-skills.sh based on the developer's AI_REVIEW_TOOL setting.
# They are intentionally NOT committed so the repo isn't branded with any
# particular AI tool's directory name.
#
# NOTE: .github/copilot-instructions.md, .github/instructions/, and
# .github/workflows/ai-pr-review.yml ARE committed — they configure GitHub
# Copilot's PR auto-review and the GitHub Actions workflow respectively,
# and they are not derived from any other file. Only the .../skills/
# subdirectory under each tool's location is gitignored.
.claude/skills/
.codex/skills/
.github/copilot/skills/

# Skills vendored from agent-skills by scripts/fetch-skills.sh.
.skills-vendor/

# ── Codebase audit output ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Audit reports are for human triage, not source-of-truth. Remove this line
# if your team prefers to commit audit baselines for historical comparison.
audit-reports/
